      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MOST EXCITING (2) is a lightly-raced but progressive colt who has been kept fresh since he made an impressive return at Cranbourne, leading from wider and getting home by 5.5 metres. This is stronger but he has the benefit of a good draw and has plenty of upside. Last-start runner-up LAMBRO MACH (5) is going well having finished within 2m of the winner in both outings since winning here. Suited up to a distance where he has yet to miss a place in four attempts including a win. WHERE IS WOODY (3) has been thereabouts of late and draws well so is a chance to break through after a good effort for a 1.5m second at this circuit and distance last start. MONTANA PRIDE (7) draws wide but is working towards a win, recording a respectable second at his most recent appearance at Ballarat.",
